rectangle "Core Business Process Details" {
  note as N1
    **User registration & login**
    1. User registration (username, email, phone, password)
    2. User login (email/password authentication)
    3. JWT token generation and management
    4. Token refresh mechanism
    5. User logout
  end note
  
  note as N2
    **Send message**
    1. Select chat target or group
    2. Enter/select message content (text, image, video, voice, file)
    3. Send message
    4. Push in real time to recipients
    5. Update message status (sent, delivered, read)
  end note
  
  note as N3
    **Start call**
    1. Select call target
    2. Initiate voice/video call request
    3. Establish WebRTC connection
    4. Maintain call session
    5. End call and record details
  end note
}

note bottom
  **Business architecture description**
  
  WhatsChat, as a real‑time messaging platform, has the following core business capabilities:
  
  1. **User management** – user registration, login, profile management, access control
  2. **Instant messaging** – multiple message types: text, image, video, voice, file
  3. **Feed & posts** (Status/Home feed) – create posts (multiple photos/videos + caption); status/home feed shows real posts from followed users with engagement ranking (like/save counts); multi-media carousel; comments in MongoDB; search in Elasticsearch
  4. **Reels** – vertical video feed for watch/complete engagement; like/save and follow overlay used for ranking and analytics
  5. **Recommendations & explore** – follow suggestions (from batch recommendation service), explore stream (hot posts), engagement-based ranking
  6. **Voice & video calls** – high‑quality real‑time calls based on WebRTC
  7. **File sharing** – upload, download, and preview for various file types
  8. **Group management** – create groups, manage members, configure group settings
  9. **Status sharing** – online/offline presence and ephemeral status updates
  10. **Contact management** – add, remove, search, organize contacts
  11. **Notification management** – message notifications, system notifications, push notifications
  12. **Platform administration** – dashboard, user management, content safety, ops monitor, analytics, system config, permission & audit
  
  Business value is delivered through real‑time communication, efficient collaboration,
  great user experience, and strong data security.
end note

